## Common Commands

- minikube start
    - cluster: minikube
    - namespace: default

- minikube delete
    - Deletes the local cluster. 

- minikube dashboard
    - good for visualizing changes/configs made to the cluster

- update existing deployment/service
    - `kubectl apply -f <name.yaml>

- Get service url
    - minikube service --url web-flask
    - minikube services are not natively accessible, the command above provides a link to the local ip:port that the service is running on.
    - https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/handbook/accessing/

- debugging failed pod
    - `kubectl get pods`
    - `kubectl --v=8 logs <pod-name-id>

- Monitor REDIS
    - `minikube service --url redis-master`
    - `redis-cli -h 127.0.0.1 -p <PORT> monitor`

- Load a local image into minikube
    - `minikube image load castrona/rq-worker:latest`
